<p>
  In his later career, John’s work with the federal government, including leadership roles
  at the General Services Administration, echoed the administrative and civic
  responsibilities once held by his colonial and frontier ancestors. He managed complex
  projects, navigated large institutions, and took on responsibilities that required both
  structure and flexibility.
</p>

<p>
  At the same time, John’s ongoing pursuit of learning—whether in GIS, data, cloud
  computing, or software engineering—reflects a willingness to keep growing and changing
  even later in life. In this sense, he stands at the frontier of a new kind of world:
  one defined not just by physical distance, but by knowledge, technology, and global
  connection.
</p>
